txt.en: <rgb=#FF0000>Completing 'Restoring the Three Kingdoms' will cancel this quest</rgb>
'I fear it will not be the last reminder they need, but do not doubt your efforts, [placeholder]. You have changed many minds in Dale today!'
You should publically deter discontented Dale-folk who are speaking against the refugees.

'In market stalls and street corners, a misguided few still murmur against the dispossessed from Rhûn, and their talk clouds the minds of others.

'If you, a hero of the war and a symbol of goodness, would address those malcontents, it would change many minds among the folk of Dale.

'Even if not all of their minds might be turned, it would do well to make those from Rhûn feel more welcome.'
A small number of Dale-folk continue to speak out against the Easterling refugees and cloud the minds of many others.
